				\begin{document}$${{\rm{n}}}_{{\rm{m}}}=\sqrt{1-{{\rm{\omega }}}_{{\rm{p}}}^{2}/({{\rm{\omega }}}^{2}+{\rm{i}}\,{\rm{\gamma }}\,{\rm{\omega }})},$$\end{document}nm=1−ωp2/(ω2+iγω),where the plasma frequency and damping factor are represented by ωp = 2.18 PHz and γ = 4.353 THz, respectively35. Ag was selected because it has a relatively low imaginary part of the dielectric constant (low absorption loss) compared to gold, platinum, and copper36.

The refractive index of silicon (nSi) is given by37:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
