				\begin{document}$${\rm{r}}=\frac{({{\rm{H}}}_{11}+{{\rm{H}}}_{12}\,{{\rm{p}}}_{{\rm{s}}}){{\rm{p}}}_{0}-({{\rm{H}}}_{21}+{{\rm{H}}}_{22}\,{{\rm{p}}}_{{\rm{s}}})}{({{\rm{H}}}_{11}+{{\rm{H}}}_{12}\,{{\rm{p}}}_{{\rm{s}}}){{\rm{p}}}_{0}+({{\rm{H}}}_{21}+{{\rm{H}}}_{22}\,{{\rm{p}}}_{{\rm{s}}})}$$\end{document}r=(H11+H12ps)p0−(H21+H22ps)(H11+H12ps)p0+(H21+H22ps)Where p0 = n0 cos φ0 (for prism) and ps = ns cos φs (for Si substrate). Also, φ0 indicates the incident angle of the electromagnetic waves from the prism to the structure.

