By increasing the number of periods, the sensitivity does not change (S = 2600 nm/RIU). In addition to the sensitivity, the study of the full width at half maximum (FWHM) of the resonance dip is another significant parameter for the performance of the sensor. A high-performance sensor should have a narrow resonant dip to achieve high resolution52. Figure 5 shows the behaviour of the FWHM as a function of the number of unit cells (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
