Variation in the FWHM as a function of the number of unit cells N at dm = 30 nm, ngas = 1.00026, nprism = 1.5, φ0 = 0°, and dgas = 4000 nm.

When the Ag layer has a thickness of 25 nm, the reflectance of the resonant dip decreases to zero, and the optical energy is consumed by absorption25. Hence, strong confined electromagnetic waves occur between the Ag and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
