The quality factor (QF), figure of merit (FoM), and detection limit (DL) are usually used to characterise the efficiency and performance of the sensor. An excellent sensor has high QF values that demonstrate the ability of the sensor to have a narrow bandwidth52. The QF can be calculated according to the following equation:11\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
